	(186,330,1,'Craig, Dalston',NULL,'I spotted a tall fellow heading towards me from amongst the usual Sunday afternoon throng of Kingsland Road, with something long and odd-looking strapped to his bike. In the blink of an eye, he was gone.\n\nIntrigued, I found myself turning around and running down the road to find out what it was...\n\nMy target turned out to be a friendly musician called Craig, on the hunt for a new pitch for his street performance. I don\'t know how he ended up in London from New Zealand, but like any good antipodean, he was travelling with a didgeridoo (and a typewriter).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','88a65396-1000-4c7c-ba88-a981830d6976',NULL),
	(187,331,1,'Thoughts on Zen Cycling',NULL,'If you find yourself become angry whilst riding your bike — whatever the reason — try counting to five before venting spleen.\n\nUsually the car/taxi/bus/pedestrian in question didn\'t mean it.\n\nAnd you might even hear an apology that would otherwise have been missed.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','42b53c34-92e2-4fd7-8703-0e80431cfd82',NULL),
	(188,332,1,'Ellie, Primrose Hill',NULL,'With the sun on my back and a smile on my face, I was on the prowl around Primrose Hill, and spotted a lovely green bike resting outside <a href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=Sesame+Whole+Foods+primrose+hill&amp;hl=en&amp;ll=51.54031,-0.156759&amp;spn=0.006106,0.012263&amp;sll=51.540711,-0.157405&amp;layer=c&amp;cid=8840682636223534362&amp;panoid=XQvWYv0VTPoLQ7OIUV7EJA&amp;cbp=13,241.73,,0,1.5&amp;gl=uk&amp;hq=Sesame+Whole+Foods+primrose+hill&amp;t=m&amp;z=17&amp;cbll=51.540719,-0.157322\">Seasame Wholefoods</a>.\n\nOut walked Ellie, who proceeded to chat to me energetically as I quizzed her about cycling, and meanwhile slotted a bottle of fruit juice into her bottle cage.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','1f5c3ea6-5f01-4f34-aed1-0b91b12c7daa',NULL),
	(189,333,1,'Raphael, Primrose Hill',NULL,'A flash of purple wheels caught my attention from the far side of Primrose Hill, and a few minutes later, I caught up with its owner as he stopped to enjoy the sunshine.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','0bf3f536-bb97-43ef-a440-4f6ffa14e1d6',NULL),
	(190,334,1,'Bill Cunningham — cycling photographer extraordinaire',NULL,'Shooting New York\'s street and catwalk fashions for over fourty years, photographer Bill Cunningham\'s favourite mode of transport has always been his bike.\n\nHe\'s now the subject of a fascinating documentary \"<a href=\"http://www.billcunninghamnewyork.co.uk\">Bill Cunningham New York</a>\", which explores his enormous body of work and paints a portrait of a loveable, if lonely, character. (We\'re talking about a guy who sleeps on a mattress amongst a room of filing cabinets containing his negatives!)\n\n\n\nDon\'t miss Bill\'s photos of cyclists for the New York Times <a href=\"http://video.nytimes.com/video/2011/09/02/fashion/100000001032512/bill-cunningham--cycles.html\">here</a>.\n\n<small>Image credit: Photo credit: First Thought Films / Zeitgeist Films</small>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','248ce65f-5c84-4c1e-a622-6ad58a5ef205',NULL),
	(191,335,1,'Drink Riding',NULL,'Swissmiss\'s <a href=\"http://www.swiss-miss.com/2012/03/bike-6-pack-bag.html\">post</a> about the  <a href=\"http://donkey-products.com/shop/de/alle/neuheiten/donkey-6-pack-fahrradtasche\">Donkey 6-pack</a> set our bikeheads a-wondering about the possibility of other non-standard bottle cages.\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-73 aligncenter\" title=\"Donkey 6 Pack\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/donkey6pack_mood_72dpi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"450\" /></p>\nAfter some extensive research, we\'re happy to report back on our <a href=\"http://www.caferacer351.com/forum/index.php?topic=995.msg27470#msg27470\">favourite</a>:\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74\" title=\"Bicycle Wine Rack\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/bicyclewinerackneuvo2-576x432.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"432\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','a1d40218-7d4b-46be-8a81-53b7b0bdfe8f',NULL),
	(192,336,1,'Bikes of San Francisco',NULL,'<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-94\" title=\"Bikes of San Francisco\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/5112789301_da50dca4bd_b-576x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"768\" />\n\nA pictorial guide to the <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/agirlnamedtor/5112789301/\">Bikes of San Francisco</a>. I feel a London version coming on...\n\n<a href=\"http://laughingsquid.com/bikes-of-san-francisco/\">Source</a> with a hat tip to <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/mertonium\">@mertonium</a> for calling it.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:46','2018-08-31 13:11:46','1c21263a-5db3-44e4-af77-e0063f175d1b',NULL),
