	(219,363,1,'A snapshot of Australia\'s early bike history',NULL,'Incredible archive photographs of Aussie bike culture circa 1890-1950 from the  State Library of New South Wales.\n\n<img src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5234/5861839155_41008e63b5_z.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\n\n<img src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5104/5862419072_7f9632f068_z.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\n\n<img src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3292/5865143840_4493e6a77d_z.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\n\n<img src=\"http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5119/5862474722_3511c8a09a_z.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\n\n<img src=\"http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3090/5861785723_941e53fbb9_z.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\n\nFrom <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/statelibraryofnsw/with/5861839155/\">Flickr</a> and the collection of the <a href=\"http://sl.nsw.gov.au\">State Library of New South Wales\n</a>Via <a href=\"http://www.brainpickings.org/index.php/2012/02/22/vintage-australian-bike-culture/\">Brain Pickings</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','5604f6c4-e766-4569-a480-0f67cf59dbcd',NULL),
	(220,364,1,'Bicycle Portraits - a photographic book',NULL,'A shot from the stunning \"<a href=\"http://www.dayonepublications.com/Bicycle_Portraits\">Bicycle Portraits</a>\" book — 162 portraits and stories of cyclists photographed by Stan Engelbrecht &amp; Nic Grobler during an epic two year journey across South Africa. The project was successfully <a href=\"http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/bicycleportraits/bicycle-portraits-a-photographic-book-part-iii-fin\">funded on Kickstarter</a> last year.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-304\" title=\"sina_mabeta_0588s-1\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/sina_mabeta_0588s-1-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-305\" title=\"aldren_muvhambe\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/aldren_muvhambe-740x492.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"492\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-307\" title=\"lucky_menzi_7220\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lucky_menzi_7220-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-308\" title=\"wilma_plaatjies_rico_syster_1769s\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/wilma_plaatjies_rico_syster_1769s-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','5e96ed56-e9e8-40cc-8cc4-7729b000ad0d',NULL),
	(221,365,1,'London Bike Kitchen',NULL,'Want to fix your bike but don\'t know where to start? The <a href=\"http://www.lbk.org.uk/\">London Bike Kitchen</a> is a new, open DIY workshop where you can work on your own bike instead of giving it to someone else.\n\nRun by Jenni Gwiazdowski, the workshop occupies a once forlorn retail unit in Hoxton, and offers courses in bike maintenance and mechanics to London\'s fast growing cycling community. Inspired by the <a href=\"http://www.bikekitchen.org/\">bike kitchens</a> of her native California, she aims to \"create a space where it is OK to learn; a comfortable environment for everyone\" — definitely a vibe that CycleLove picked up on our visit.\n\n<em>What bike(s) do you ride?</em>\nI ride a 2008 women\'s LeMond, an Alpina Spranghina and have a vintage Claud Butler frame that I will build up someday.\n\n<em>The age old question: helmet or no helmet?</em>\nDepends on the weather, where I\'m going or how long I spent on my hair. Sometimes all three.\n\n<em>What do you love most about cycling in London? Any favourite rides?</em>\nI love the fact that my bike can take me anywhere, usually faster than the tube or bus. I enjoy cycling the River Lea.\n\n<em>If you were elected Mayor next month, what changes would you make to transport policy to improve life for London\'s cyclists?</em>\nIn my wildest fantasies I would ban private cars from the road. Public transport only. I believe air pollution is a giant of a problem that affects ALL Londoners - pedestrians, cyclists, and drivers alike.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-336\" title=\"lbk 9\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-9-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-330\" title=\"lbk 5\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-5-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-332\" title=\"lbk 13\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-13-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-331\" title=\"lbk 11\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-11-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-335\" title=\"lbk 4\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-41-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-337\" title=\"lbk 3\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-3-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-338\" title=\"lbk 14\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-14-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-342\" title=\"lbk 7\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lbk-7-740x740.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"740\" />\n\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','afcf9536-9252-4ad2-b15d-1e5c9b59680a',NULL),
	(222,366,1,'Andreas, London Cyclist',NULL,'One of the inspirations for starting CycleLove was the wealth of amazing bike blogs springing up around London, not least that of Andreas Kambanis, aka the <a href=\"http://www.londoncyclist.co.uk/\">London Cyclist</a>, who I snapped on a slightly grim \'Spring\' day outside the Hayward Gallery on the South Bank.\n\n<em>What came first, cycling or blogging?</em>\nCycling came way before blogging for me. I tried it, loved it and then wanted to know more about it. When I discovered there wasn\'t really anything out there for the everyday cyclist like myself, I set it up.\n\n<em>What bike(s) do you ride?</em>\nI ride a Raleigh Ti frame that I built up about 8 months ago. It\'s a great single speed bike that allows me to power my way around London without worrying too much about maintenance and things going wrong. Also, it looks a little old and worn so I think it makes less of a target for thieves.\n\n<em>The age old question: helmet or no helmet?</em>\nFor me it\'s a personal decision but I choose to not wear a helmet. I don\'t really want to go in to it too much as I feel it\'s an argument that has been heard so many times over! (Editor\'s note: We agree. Take the <a href=\"http://www.lfgss.com/thread1525.html\">3,000+ responses on this LFGSS forum thread</a> as a starting point)\n\n<em>What do you love most about cycling in London?</em>\nI cycle in London because I\'m lazy. I don\'t like walking to the tube, waiting for a train and then arriving not exactly at my destination. With the bike I can pull up right next to where I\'m meeting someone and I have the freedom to make my own timetable. Plus, London is a gorgeous and fascinating city and I couldn\'t imagine not seeing it everyday from the saddle.\n\n<em>If you were elected Mayor next month, what changes would you make to transport policy to improve life for London\'s cyclist?</em>\nAs Mayor, I\'d force all heavy goods vehicles to have warning devices for when a cyclist is in the danger zone. Also, even though it would make me hugely unpopular, I would extend the congestion charging zone. I believe driving a car in central London is madness.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','37f654eb-d5d7-4713-9d8f-eed26c7b4a15',NULL),
	(223,367,1,'How would you persuade a friend to start cycling?',NULL,'Those cycle-crazy folk at Bikeminded are <a href=\"http://www.bikeminded.org/film-competition/competition-detail/\">on the hunt for a short film</a> to inspire people to change from two feet to two wheels.\n\n\n\nWhich raises the question: how would you persuade a friend or loved one to start cycling?\n\nWhen I moved to London it took me six months to pluck up the courage to start commuting by bike. I couldn\'t see past the supposedly terrifying buses that I saw cyclists sandwiched between. But with all of my friends nagging me about it, eventually I bought a second-hand number and started cycling. Fast-forward a few months, and I owned three bikes, cycled to work daily, and even rode London to Brighton just for the hell of it. (Non-cyclists, that\'s something you might not understand, yet...)\n\nCycleLove was christened so because I want to get people on bikes by showing them they don\'t have to be afraid. And, as any good psychologist will tell you, fear is the opposite of love. Armed with some simple <a href=\"http://www.bikeradar.com/gear/article/technique-road-positioning-197/\">facts about the road and holding your position on it</a>, no-one should be intimidated by the thought of cycling.\n\nUpdate: a brilliant suggestion from <a href=\"http://ispeakbike.blogspot.co.uk/\">I Speak Bike</a>:\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>@<a href=\"https://twitter.com/cyclelovehq\">cyclelovehq</a> I\'ve been taking friends out on the back of my tandem and showing them their commute route so they can see how easy it is.</p>— Jude Brosnan (@ISpeakBike) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ISpeakBike/status/192920536244957185\">April 19, 2012</a></blockquote>\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','c9bf0175-579b-49b1-a5ae-8d38307d79bc',NULL),
	(224,368,1,'An invisible bicycle helmet?',NULL,'Designed by Anna Haupt and Terese Alstin at the Faculty of Engineering at Lund University in Sweden, <a href=\"http://www.hovding.com/en/how\">Hovding</a> is a personal airbag for cyclists.\n<blockquote>\"Bicycling is something we do every day and there\'s a sense of freedom that goes with it. Although people are well aware of the risks on the roads, the vast majority are choosing to bicycle without a helmet. When it comes down to it, people do really want to protect their heads in road accidents, but there are limits. It isn\'t the bicyclists who need to change, it\'s the product.\"</blockquote>\nHidden inside a waterproof collar around your neck, Hovding is trigged by abnormal movement, inflating in 1/10 of a second to (almost) encase the wearer\'s head. However we\'re not sure what happens if you should land on your face...\n\nCynicism aside however, it\'s not often that the worlds of cycling safety and cycling fashion collide, and Hovding proves that it is possible to be stylish and protected.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-362\" title=\"hovding-beforejpg-f50597488b3cac88\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/hovding-beforejpg-f50597488b3cac88-740x987.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"987\" />\n\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','ecbf8478-eb7c-479f-9127-1a83234ff05a',NULL),
	(225,369,1,'Launch party update: it\'s a sellout',NULL,'An important update tomorrow\'s (Saturday 21st) launch party at <a href=\"http://www.lookmumnohands.com/\">Look mum no hands!</a>\n\nIf you\'re lucky enough to have secured tickets, please arrive by 7pm sharp for the <a href=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/journal/2012/bill-cunningham-cycling-photographer-extraordinaire/\">Bill Cunningham New York</a> screening. This part of the evening is now sold out, so the earlier you arrive, the more likely you are to nab a seat.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-410\" title=\"Dress to impress\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/bikes_wide_bw-740x422.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"422\" />\n\n<strong>Dress to impress:</strong>\nDon\'t have a ticket for the film? Fear not, the party opens its doors to anyone and everyone between 8.30-11pm, with a vintage DJ set from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/auntie_maureen\">Auntie Maureen</a>, and reggae from CycleLove\'s own James Greig.\n\nIn keeping with the fashion theme of Bill Cunningham New York, we\'re encouraging (but not forcing) you to DRESS TO IMPRESS. So put on something nice, and head down to Look Mum No Hands on Old Street for a little rockabilly, 50\'s r &amp; b and 60\'s boogaloo and soul.\n\nRemember, to enter our best-dressed cyclist competition (with amazing prizes from <a href=\"http://www.vulpine.cc/\">Vulpine</a> and <a href=\"http://sogrenibikes.com/\">Sogreni</a>), jump on your bike, and arrive around 6-6.30pm, so we have time to take your photo. We\'ll be blogging all of the photos next week, and the people who get the most Facebook likes will be deemed the winners.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:49','2018-08-31 13:11:49','9e61bb12-bf7a-4d34-b07f-d8322eed1eb6',NULL),
	(226,370,1,'David Bennett\'s Nature Factory',NULL,'\"The Nature Factory is a new approach to manufacturing being a small scale mobile factory looking at a future of “hyper-local” production. It is able to with the help of the general public extract from its surroundings, the beach in this instance, raw resources to produce a mouldable material that can be used to make furniture for the beach.\"\n\nThis thought-provoking project from designer/engineer/maker <a href=\"http://www.davidgbennett.co.uk/\">David Bennett</a>, based around a bicycle rickshaw, poses some interesting questions about our attitudes to manufacturing materials. Nature Factory produces limecrete, a weak form of concrete, by combining  hydrated Lime and sand/aggregate, which is then cast to make stools.\n\nWhy do we anthropomorphise and add emotive qualities to some? Categorising them into binary opposites, natural and artificial? As all materials are from the same source, the environment, why are some more emotive or valuable than others? If we were to once again link the source and the material, how would we perceive them?\n\n<a href=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Nature-Factory-Long-Text.pdf\">Read more about Nature Factory (PDF)</a>\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-453\" title=\"-1\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/1-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-454\" title=\"-2\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/2-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-454\" title=\"-4\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/4-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-454\" title=\"-5\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/5-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-454\" title=\"-6\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/6-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','d1c16ffc-bd14-41bd-aed8-e29240928d5a',NULL),
	(227,371,1,'Launch party recap',NULL,'A huge thanks to everyone who came down to <a href=\"http://www.lookmumnohands.com/\">Look Mum No Hands!</a> on Saturday for our first ever event. We were delighted to have a completely full house for the screening of Bill Cunningham New York.\n\nStay tuned for photos from the best-dressed cyclist competition and more shots of an amazing tall bike in action (scroll down for a sneak peak)...\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Had great time at launch party for @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/cyclelovehq\">cyclelovehq</a> watching the Bill Cunningham New York screening, he is truly amazing person!!!!</p>— Gosia (@gosia_sikon) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gosia_sikon/status/193844256664850432\">April 21, 2012</a></blockquote>\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Enjoyed the Bill Cunningham New York screening last night thanks to @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/cyclelovehq\">cyclelovehq</a> &amp; @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/j_greig\">j_greig</a> — recommend film to watch.</p>— Tudinh (@Tudinh) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Tudinh/status/194069885733707780\">April 22, 2012</a></blockquote>\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>@<a href=\"https://twitter.com/LadyVelo\">LadyVelo</a> I know, me too! Loved the film, was so gorgeous. Bill seems like such a sweetie! @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/1ookmumnohands\">1ookmumnohands</a> @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/cyclelovehq\">cyclelovehq</a></p>— Jo Halstead (@jo_halstead) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jo_halstead/status/193828852043235329\">April 21, 2012</a></blockquote>\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>The Bill Cunningham film was excellent! Thank you @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/cyclelovehq\">cyclelovehq</a> &amp; @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/1ookmumnohands\">1ookmumnohands</a> for a lovely evening :)</p>— Jools Walker (@LadyVelo) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/LadyVelo/status/193806620076154880\">April 21, 2012</a></blockquote>\n\n\n<a href=\"http: