	(228,372,1,'My Raleigh',NULL,'I shot a few test images yesterday for tonight\'s launch photo-shoot, of which this is probably my favourite. She\'s a bit of a mish-mash of parts (including a beautiful Italmanubri quill stem), and none of the components even match, but the colour always makes me smile.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','8b52306e-0adc-4092-ba5f-d6443b9a9ea2',NULL),
	(229,373,1,'Wren bicycles — small and beautiful',NULL,'If you\'re looking for a new compact bike with a vintage twist,  this beauty from <a href=\"http://wrenbicycles.co.uk/\">Wren Bicycles</a> might fit the bill.\n<blockquote>\"The Wren Original combines the charm of vintage style with the practicality of contemporary design and components. Purpose-built for city cycling, this sturdy 3-speed model is equipped with bespoke luggage racks to carry all you need for your day.\"</blockquote>\n<a href=\"http://sargentandco.wordpress.com/2012/03/30/wren-bicycle-for-sale/\">According to Sargent and Co</a> (North London specialists in classic road bikes but now selling new bikes too) it doesn\'t ride like it\'s small, or twitch like some of its competitors. With a Brooks sprung saddle and removable racks, it\'s practical too.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','29835d4c-6870-4e06-bcda-2dfc70749580',NULL),
	(230,374,1,'Julian, Kath and Harlow, Londoners on Bikes',NULL,'As the election race between Boris and Ken hots up in London, <a href=\"http://www.londonersonbikes.org.uk/\">Londoners on Bikes</a> are likewise stepping up their campaign to raise awareness of cycle safety issues, and have cleverly targeted the cute-vote by enlisting their pets.\n\nOn an unrelated note, I\'ve decided to put my pet-photography career plans on hold, for now. Too much like hard work.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-496\" title=\"londonersonbikes_small_x4\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/londonersonbikes_small_x4-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img title=\"Dog\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/londonersonbikes_dog_-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','00db4d38-f87d-41b3-9e86-87ec0c41bb68',NULL),
	(231,375,1,'Louie-Blu, outside Look Mum No Hands',NULL,'We spotted Louie-Blu getting his BMX fixed at Look Mum No Hands on Old Street.\n\nLouie, if you\'re reading this, <a href=\"mailto:info@cyclelove.net?Subject=Louie-Blu\">please click here to email us</a>, so we can send you a limited edition CycleLove poster!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','d6b768e8-9cf8-4940-ba62-a72f65a9ca48',NULL),
	(232,376,1,'Judge the first CycleLove best-dressed competition',NULL,'Due to the rain (and possibly irrate Addison Lee taxi drivers in bus lanes), the turnout for our inaugral best-dressed competition at our launch party was lower than hoped.\n\n<strong>However, we still need you to vote for your favourite by clicking the \'Like\' button.</strong>\n\nFirst prize is a beautifully minimal bike bell from <a href=\"http://sogrenibikes.com/\">Sogreni</a> — so, check out the photos below and get voting!\n\n<del>UPDATE: Voting ends Tuesday 1st May at 10am.</del>\n\nUPDATE: Voting is over, and the winner is <a href=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/journal/2012/petor/\">Petor</a>. Well dressed, sir!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','fb032388-baa3-4b86-ae07-8599c2927167',NULL),
	(233,377,1,'Neil, tokyobike',NULL,'Founded in 2002 in a sleepy  Tokyo suburb, <a href=\"http://tokyobike.co.uk/\">tokyobike</a> is a small bike manufacturer which has recently opened stores in Berlin, London and Paris.\n\nTheir bikes are beautifully simple, with a compact frame, and (something that\'s not immediately obvious in photos) smaller than usual wheels. The result is a light and manoeuvrable  bike that\'s perfectly suited for city-riding.\n\n<img title=\"tokyobikes 3\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-3-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img title=\"tokyobikes 5\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-5-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\nPossibly the most photogenic bike store that CycleLove has yet encountered, <a href=\"http://tokyobike.co.uk/contact.htm\">tokyobike London</a> is cannily located at the cycling/design hub of Tabernacle Street in Shoreditch. The store isn\'t just about bikes though, as you can also buy a range of beautiful Japanese products, sourced from craftspeople around their Japanese headquarters.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-563\" title=\"tokyobikes 2\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-2-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-565\" title=\"tokyobikes 4\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-4-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n \n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-567\" title=\"tokyobikes 8\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-8-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img title=\"tokyobikes 9\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-91-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\n<img title=\"tokyobikes 10\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/tokyobikes-10-740x493.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" />\n\nWe asked Neil, co-owner/director of tokyobike UK, about cycling in London...\n\n<em>What bike(s) do you ride?</em>\n<a href=\"http://tokyobike.co.uk/bikes.htm\">A tokyobike CS </a>- colour depends on my mood!\n\n<em>The age old question: helmet or no helmet?</em>\nI\'m a recent convert to helmets - essential kit.\n\n<em>What do you love most about cycling in London? Any favourite rides?</em>\nIt\'s the only way to get around. London is too big a city to cover on foot and too great a city to miss out on stuck behind a windscreen.\n\nThe five minute cycle from my flat in the Brunswick Centre to <a href=\"http://lantanacafe.co.uk/\">Lantana</a> (favourite cafe) on a Sunday morning is up there. Riding through the grand squares of Islington, getting on the the Grand Union and stopping at <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/london/restaurants/venue/2%3A26732/towpath\">Towpath Cafe </a>for breakfast is pretty good. But if I have to pick one it would be the <a href=\"http://tweedrun.com/\">Tweed Run</a> - London at its very best.\n\n<em>If you were elected Mayor, what changes would you make to transport policy to improve life for London\'s cyclists?</em>\nBan private cars from central london (except for disabled people etc..). I love to drive but its pretty obvious London would be a better place if it became a cycle city.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:50','2018-08-31 13:11:50','94b9e81e-ba5d-4e6a-91f6-87a178ce6d3e',NULL),
