	(256,400,1,'Bike-centric junction, Tucson, Arizona',NULL,'What would happen if bikes were given priority over cars at busy intersections?\n\nThe city of Tucson is chasing the \"platinum\" level of bicycle-friendliness awards from the League of American Bicyclists, which would put it in the same company as other bike-friendly cities such as Portland, Oregon.\n\nAt this junction, the cycle lane occupies most of the road, and continues on into a dedicated cycle-route which allows riders to cruise safely on into town. Love it.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-724\" title=\"tuscon_junction\" src=\"http://www.cyclelove.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/tuscon_junction.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"740\" height=\"553\" />',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:51','2018-08-31 13:11:51','d5f432db-dbe5-4ffc-ab7a-df96149f6951',NULL),
