	(266,410,1,'Gary, Pedals for Progress',NULL,'What to do with that unwanted old bike in your back yard?\n\n<a href=\"http://www.p4p.org/\">Pedals for Progress</a> have recycled over 130,000 bikes destined for US landfills, improving lives in the developing world by shipping them to developing countries like Nicaragua, Ghana and Vietnam. Their <a href=\"http://www.p4p.org/?page_id=155\">business model</a> goes beyond just the bikes, sewing machines are also recycled, and spare parts sent with the bikes to ensure that the new owner has everything he or she needs to maintain their new (old) bike.\n\nFind out about Pedals for Progress <a href=\"http://www.p4p.org/?page_id=159\">bike collections process</a> and <a href=\"http://www.p4p.org/?page_id=159\">collection schedule</a>, or <a href=\"http://www.p4p.org/?page_id=380\">make a donation</a>.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2018-08-31 13:11:53','2018-08-31 13:11:53','ac12f1d4-ac0e-44a6-ad66-0d9260f86276',NULL),
