	(365,'field',2,1,' want to fix your bike but don t know where to start the london bike kitchen is a new open diy workshop where you can work on your own bike instead of giving it to someone else run by jenni gwiazdowski the workshop occupies a once forlorn retail unit in hoxton and offers courses in bike maintenance and mechanics to london s fast growing cycling community inspired by the bike kitchens of her native california she aims to create a space where it is ok to learn a comfortable environment for everyone definitely a vibe that cyclelove picked up on our visit what bike s do you ride i ride a 2008 women s lemond an alpina spranghina and have a vintage claud butler frame that i will build up someday the age old question helmet or no helmet depends on the weather where i m going or how long i spent on my hair sometimes all three what do you love most about cycling in london any favourite rides i love the fact that my bike can take me anywhere usually faster than the tube or bus i enjoy cycling the river lea if you were elected mayor next month what changes would you make to transport policy to improve life for london s cyclists in my wildest fantasies i would ban private cars from the road public transport only i believe air pollution is a giant of a problem that affects all londoners pedestrians cyclists and drivers alike '),
