	(370,'field',2,1,' the nature factory is a new approach to manufacturing being a small scale mobile factory looking at a future of hyper local production it is able to with the help of the general public extract from its surroundings the beach in this instance raw resources to produce a mouldable material that can be used to make furniture for the beach this thought provoking project from designer engineer maker david bennett based around a bicycle rickshaw poses some interesting questions about our attitudes to manufacturing materials nature factory produces limecrete a weak form of concrete by combining hydrated lime and sand aggregate which is then cast to make stools why do we anthropomorphise and add emotive qualities to some categorising them into binary opposites natural and artificial as all materials are from the same source the environment why are some more emotive or valuable than others if we were to once again link the source and the material how would we perceive them read more about nature factory pdf '),
