	(377,'field',2,1,' founded in 2002 in a sleepy tokyo suburb tokyobike is a small bike manufacturer which has recently opened stores in berlin london and paris their bikes are beautifully simple with a compact frame and something that s not immediately obvious in photos smaller than usual wheels the result is a light and manoeuvrable bike that s perfectly suited for city riding possibly the most photogenic bike store that cyclelove has yet encountered tokyobike london is cannily located at the cycling design hub of tabernacle street in shoreditch the store isn t just about bikes though as you can also buy a range of beautiful japanese products sourced from craftspeople around their japanese headquarters we asked neil co owner director of tokyobike uk about cycling in london what bike s do you ride a tokyobike cs colour depends on my mood the age old question helmet or no helmet i m a recent convert to helmets essential kit what do you love most about cycling in london any favourite rides it s the only way to get around london is too big a city to cover on foot and too great a city to miss out on stuck behind a windscreen the five minute cycle from my flat in the brunswick centre to lantana favourite cafe on a sunday morning is up there riding through the grand squares of islington getting on the the grand union and stopping at towpath cafe for breakfast is pretty good but if i have to pick one it would be the tweed run london at its very best if you were elected mayor what changes would you make to transport policy to improve life for london s cyclists ban private cars from central london except for disabled people etc i love to drive but its pretty obvious london would be a better place if it became a cycle city '),
